  <summary date="2022-09-13T14:34:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Multiple Firearm Sales Reporting Modernization Act of 2022

This bill expands reporting requirements with respect to sales or dispositions of multiple firearms.

Currently, a federal firearms licensee (e.g., a gun dealer) must report multiple sales or dispositions of pistols or revolvers to the same person within five business days. This bill requires a federal firearms licensee to report multiple sales or dispositions of any firearms to the same person within five business days.</summary>
